<doc id="1027" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=1027" title="Kanchi Shankaracharya Jayendra Saraswathi in custody">
<h1>Kanchi Shankaracharya Jayendra Saraswathi in custody</h1>
♡❤Thursday, November 18 2004, Kancheepuram, Tamil Nadu, India.♡❤ Kanchi Mutt seer Sri Jayendra Saraswathi has been remanded to 5 day's police custody in the South Indian town of &lt;a href="w%3AVellore"&gt;Vellore&lt;/a&gt;.

&lt;a href="w%3AJayendra%20Saraswathi"&gt;Jayendra Saraswathi&lt;/a&gt; is the senior &lt;a href="w%3APontiff"&gt;pontiff&lt;/a&gt; of the 2500 year old Kanchi Mutt, situated in Kancheepuram in the &lt;a href="w%3ASouth%20India"&gt;South Indian state&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href="w%3ATamil%20Nadu"&gt;Tamil Nadu&lt;/a&gt;. He is also a prominent religious leader both because of the stature of the Mutt and the Mutt's large number of devotees but also for his active but unsuccessful role in resolving the &lt;a href="w%3ABabri%20Mosque"&gt;Ayodhya dispute&lt;/a&gt;.

The seer was arrested on 11 November, 2004 at Mahboobnagar, about 150 km from &lt;a href="w%3AHyderabad"&gt;Hyderabad&lt;/a&gt; of directing the murder of A.Sankararaman, a former Manager of the Mutt.
&lt;a href="w%3ATamil%20Nadu"&gt;Tamil Nadu&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="w%3AChief%20Minister"&gt;Chief Minister&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="w%3AJayalalitha"&gt;J. Jayalalithaa&lt;/a&gt; said on Wednesday, November 17 2004 that the arrest was made since they had solid evidence. 
The evidence was in the form of a statement by two of the prime accused in the case confirming his invovlement, huge sum of money drawn to pay for the murder and telephone conversations with the killers.

