<doc id="1089" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=1089" title="Spanish tourist fatally shot in Rio de Janeiro">
<h1>Spanish tourist fatally shot in Rio de Janeiro</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Spanish%20tourist%20fatally%20shot%20in%20Rio%20de%20Janeiro&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

RIO DE JANEIRO – ' -
Juan Carlos Concero, aged 34, a &lt;a href="w%3ASpain"&gt;Spanish&lt;/a&gt; tourist, was shot in the head during an assault in &lt;a href="w%3ARio%20de%20Janeiro"&gt;Rio de Janeiro&lt;/a&gt; today. 
He was carried to Souza Aguiar Hospital where he was in a &lt;a href="w%3Acoma"&gt;coma&lt;/a&gt;, breathing with the help of life support machines. Hours later doctors pronounced him braindead.

The Brazilian police offices in charge of the case announced the arrest of three man suspected of shooting Concero.

