<doc id="1103" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=1103" title="Brazilian economist Celso Furtado dies">
<h1>Brazilian economist Celso Furtado dies</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Brazilian%20economist%20Celso%20Furtado%20dies&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

RIO DE JANEIRO – The Brazilian Economist &lt;a href="w%3ACelso%20Furtado"&gt;Celso Furtado&lt;/a&gt;, aged 84, has died today between 11 and 11:30 am, in his apartament in &lt;a href="w%3ARio%20de%20Janeiro"&gt;Rio de Janeiro&lt;/a&gt;. 
According to ABr (Government Brazilian news Agency) Celso Furtado was victim of a heart attack. 

He will be buried tomorrow at São João Batista cemetery, Rio de Janeiro at 12:00.

