<doc id="1168" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=1168" title="Ukrainian opposition leader calls for police and army to join revolution">
<h1>Ukrainian opposition leader calls for police and army to join revolution</h1>
<ul>
BULLET::::- Steven Lee Myers. "&lt;a href="http%3A//nytimes.com/2004/11/29/international/europe/29cnd-ukra.html%3Fhp%26amp%3Bex%3D1101790800%26amp%3Ben%3D93f5ca7f542c1962%26amp%3Bei%3D5094%26amp%3Bpartner%3Dwikipedia"&gt;Departing Ukrainian President Would Support New Election&lt;/a&gt;" — &lt;i&gt;&lt;span class="interwiki-link-foreign"&gt;&lt;a href="w%3AThe%20New%20York%20Times"&gt;The New York Times&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/i&gt;, November 29, 2004
BULLET::::- Julius Strauss. "&lt;a href="http%3A//www.telegraph.co.uk/news/main.jhtml%3Bsessionid%3DIPCARNCMT0FRRQFIQMGSM5WAVCBQWJVC%3Fxml%3D/news/2004/11/24/wukra24.xml%26amp%3BsSheet%3D/news/2004/11/24/ixnewstop.html"&gt;Revolution in Ukraine&lt;/a&gt;" — &lt;i&gt;&lt;span class="interwiki-link-foreign"&gt;&lt;a href="w%3AThe%20Daily%20Telegraph%20%28United%20Kingdom%29"&gt;The Daily Telegraph (United Kingdom)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/i&gt;, November 25, 2004 &lt;span style="font-family: sans-serif; cursor: default; color: #0000CD; font-size: 1.2em; font-weight: bold;" title="This source has been taken offline but was used in the creation of this article before it went offline."&gt;(&lt;span class="video_source" style="color: #FF3300;font-size: 0.7em; position: relative; bottom: 0.1em"&gt;Source link broken&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;

