<h1>National Academy of Sciences recommends manned Hubble repair</h1>
♡❤December 9, 2004♡❤. A &lt;a href="w%3ANational%20Academy%20of%20Sciences"&gt;National Academy of Sciences&lt;/a&gt; committee has recommended that the National Aeronautical and Space Administration send astronauts to repair the Hubble Space Telescope. The Academy's National Research Council assembled the committee. The committee's chairman is &lt;a href="w%3ANew%20Jersey%20Institute%20of%20Technology"&gt;New Jersey Institute of Technology&lt;/a&gt; physics professor Dr. Louis J. Lanzerotti.

