<doc id="2030" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=2030" title="Battle of the Bulge reenacted in Belgium">
<h1>Battle of the Bulge reenacted in Belgium</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Battle%20of%20the%20Bulge%20reenacted%20in%20Belgium&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

&lt;a href="w%3ABastogne"&gt;Bastogne&lt;/a&gt; – 
A celebration held here today marked the 60th anniversary of the &lt;a href="w%3ABattle%20of%20the%20Bulge"&gt;Battle of the Bulge&lt;/a&gt; &amp;mdash; a key battle for American forces during &lt;a href="w%3AWorld%20War%20II"&gt;World War II&lt;/a&gt;. With thousands&amp;mdash;including &lt;a href="w%3AAlbert%20II%20of%20Belgium"&gt;King Albert II&lt;/a&gt; of Belgium&amp;mdash;in attendance at the Mardasson monument, the festivities included a parade of military vehicles, soldiers that participated in the battle, as well as a light show.

A memorable moment in the history of the battle &amp;mdash; &lt;a href="w%3AAnthony%20McAuliffe"&gt;General MacAuliffe's&lt;/a&gt; reply "Nuts!" to the German request for surrender &amp;mdash; was commemorated with the throwing of nuts into the audience. Many American veterans attended and participated in the celebration. 

