<doc id="3358" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=3358" title="Yahoo triples its quarterly profit on strong advertising revenue">
<h1>Yahoo triples its quarterly profit on strong advertising revenue</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Yahoo%20triples%20its%20quarterly%20profit%20on%20strong%20advertising%20revenue&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

&lt;a href="Yahoo"&gt;Yahoo!&lt;/a&gt;, the world's favorite Internet destination, reported $373 million in net income for the three month period ended December 31. Revenues were $1,078 million for the fourth quarter of 2004, a 62 percent increase compared to $664 million for the same period of 2003. “We are attracting more and more users to Yahoo!’s network of services and driving their usage deeper with more relevant products and services. This deeper usage is the real magic behind the surpassing of our financial objectives,” explained Susan Decker, the company's chief financial officer.

<h3>More Details</h3>
<ul>
BULLET::::- Revenues excluding &lt;a href="w%3Atraffic%20acquisition%20costs"&gt;traffic acquisition costs&lt;/a&gt; (“TAC”) were $785 million for the fourth quarter of 2004, a 54 percent increase compared to $511 million for the same period of 2003
BULLET::::- &lt;a href="w%3AGross%20profit"&gt;Gross profit&lt;/a&gt; for the fourth quarter of 2004 was $691 million, a 56 percent increase compared to $443 million for the same period of 2003
BULLET::::- &lt;a href="w%3AOperating%20income"&gt;Operating income&lt;/a&gt; for the fourth quarter of 2004 was $235 million, a 149 percent increase compared to $94 million for the same period of 2003
BULLET::::- Operating income before &lt;a href="w%3Adepreciation"&gt;depreciation&lt;/a&gt; and amortization for the fourth quarter of 2004 was $327 million, an 84 percent increase compared to $178 million for the same period of]] 2003

</ul>
